            =  Angad Bedi \n| image           = Angad Bedi gracing \u2018Filmfare Glamour & Style Awards 2016\u2019.jpg\n| imagesize       = \n| alt             = \n| caption         = Bedi gracing \u2018Filmfare Glamour & Style Awards October 2016\u2019\n| birthname       = \n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1983|02|06}}<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/news/bollywood-news/article/neha-dhupia-and-angad-bedi-age-and-date-of-birth-all-details-about-the-celebrity-couple/226649|title=Neha Dhupia and Angad Bedi age and date of birth: All details about the celebrity couple|access-date=2018-05-14|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n| birth_place      = [[Delhi]], [[India]]\n| death_date       = <!-- {{Death date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} Death date then birth -->\n| death_place      = \n| othername       = \n| occupation      = Actor\n| yearsactive     = 2004-present\n| parents         = [[Bishan Singh Bedi]]\n| spouse          = {{marriage|[[Neha Dhupia]]|2018}}\n| children =  1\n| website         = \n}}\n'''Angad Singh Bedi''' (born 6 February 1983) is an [[Indian film]] actor and model.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/rumoured-couple-nora-fatehi-angad-bedi-share-the-same-birthday-wish-each-other-in-the-sweetest-way-possible/articleshow/57016419.cms|title=Rumoured couple Nora Fatehi, Angad Bedi share the same birthday; wish each other in the sweetest way possible - Times of India|publisher=}}</ref> He made his Hindi film debut in 2011 with ''[[F.A.L.T.U]]''. Angad made his television debut with ''[[Kaya Taran]]'', an adaptation of a [[Malayalam]] short story by [[N. S. Madhavan]], ''[[When Big Tree Falls]], The Earth Is Bound To Shake''.<ref name=\"indiatimes.com\">{{cite web|url=http://info.indiatimes.com/1984/5.html|title=Timesofindia > 1984 Anti-Sikh Riots|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012 Angad was arrested at a rave party at a Suburban Juhu Hotel, he tested positive for the consumption of cannabis and ecstasy and was later released on bail.\nAngad has also appeared in a cooking show called ''Cook Na Kaho'' on [[Star One (Indian TV channel)|Star One]]. He hosted the first season of the reality television show ''[[Emotional Atyachar]]'' on [[UTV Bindass]] before being replaced by [[Pravesh Rana]]. He participated in Season 3 of Colors' show ''[[Fear Factor: Khatron Ke Khiladi]]''. Angad is currently working on ''The Little Godfather'', directed by Joy Augustine. He is also part of the movie [[Soorma (film)|Soorma]], the biopic of the Indian hockey player [[Sandeep Singh]] playing the Indian field hockey player Bikramjit Singh. Angad is best known for his performances in works such as ''[[Ungli]]'' (2014), and ''[[Pink (2016 film)|PINK]]'' (2016).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/angad-singh-bedi-pink-is-the-new-black/article9115123.ece|title=Angad Singh Bedi: 'Pink is the new black'|first=Allan Moses|last=Rodricks|date=16 September 2016|publisher=[[The Hindu]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/pink-is-actually-for-the-men-angad-bedi/story-gcB4oosKNeIH4yXWD61HkM.html|title=Pink is actually for the men: Angad Bedi|date=16 September 2016|publisher=}}</ref> In 2017 he starred as lead in [[Amazon Video|Amazon]] [[List of original programs distributed by Amazon|original series]] series ''[[Inside Edge (2017 TV series)|Inside Edge]]''.<ref>{{Cite web | title = Angad Bedi reveals he got inspired from MS Dhoni for his role in 'Inside Edge' |work = [[Daily News and Analysis]] | date =2017-07-14 | accessdate = 2017-07-17 | url = http://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-angad-bedi-reveals-he-got-inspired-from-ms-dhoni-for-his-role-in-inside-edge-2502363 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | title = Hope someone casts Richa Chadha with me in a film: Angad Bedi |work = [[Hindustan Times]] | date =2017-07-15 | accessdate = 2017-07-17 | first=Sweta | last=Kaushal| url = http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/hope-someone-casts-richa-chadha-with-me-in-a-film-angad-bedi/story-AR42rK10E5ns8lDVYcOlbO.html }}</ref> He was also seen In ''[[Tiger Zinda Hai]]'' with [[Salman Khan]].<ref>{{Cite web | title = Angad Bedi to get trained under a professional trainer for Tiger Zinda Hai |work = [[Bollywood Hungama]] | date =2017-07-14 | accessdate = 2017-07-17 | url = http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/features/wow-angad-bedi-get-trained-professional-trainer-tiger-zinda-hai/ }}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nAngad was born to noted Indian cricketer [[Bishan Singh Bedi]]. He played cricket up to Under-19 level for Delhi. He studied at Gyan Bharati School, Saket, New Delhi and graduated from [[St. Stephen's College, Delhi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/off-the-field/Yuvraj-Singh-bats-for-Angad-Bedis-new-movie/articleshow/45219955.cms|title=Yuvraj Singh bats for Angad Bedi's new movie - Times of India|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"cricketcountry.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.cricketcountry.com/photos/others/photo-angad-bedi-wishes-father-bishan-singh-bedi-on-birthday-333633|title=PHOTO: Angad Bedi wishes father Bishan Singh Bedi on birthday|date=25 September 2015|publisher=}}</ref>  Subsequently, he began a career in modelling, and ventured into acting.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmfare.com/interviews/quick-5-with-angad-bedi-15606.html|title=Quick 5 with Angad Bedi|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\n[[File:Angad Neha.jpg|thumb|Bedi with his wife [[Neha Dhupia]]]]\nAngad Bedi has one elder sister, Neha, and two older half-siblings from Bishan's previous marriage \u2013 a half-sister named Gillinder and a half-brother named Gavasinder.<ref name=\"cricketcountry.com\"/> Angad Bedi began dating Neha Dhupia while he was in a relationship with Nora Fatehi, Neha eventually got pregnant and the couple decided to get married 3 months into the pregnancy in a private ceremony at a Gurudwara on May 10, 2018. On November 18, 2018, she gave birth to their first child, a girl, Mehr Dhupia Bedi<ref>{{cite news|title=Neha Dhupia and Angad Bedi are wife and husband now|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/neha-dhupia-and-angad-bedi-are-wife-and-husband-now-see-pics-from-wedding/story-6OA83592vnBPWIUS0txrcK.html|work=[[The Hindustan Times]]|date=May 10, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Films===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" width=60%\n!scope=\"col\" width=\"10%\"| Year\n!scope=\"col\"| Title\n!scope=\"col\"| Role\n!scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n!scope=\"col\" width=\"10%\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| 2004 || ''[[Kaya Taran]]''|| Preet || ||\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[F.A.L.T.U]]'' || Niranjan \"Nanj\" Nair || ||\n|-\n| 2013 || ''[[Rangeelay]]'' || Ricky || Punjabi language film || <ref>https://www.hindustantimes.com/chandigarh/love-gets-complicated/story-akxAdjiBz6PDOfsAsMEXkN.html</ref>\n| 2014 || ''[[Ungli]]'' || Kalim || ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2016 || ''[[Pink (2016 film)|Pink]]'' || Rajveer Singh || ||\n|-\n|| ''[[Dear Zindagi]]'' || Sid || ||\n|-\n| 2017 || ''[[Tiger Zinda Hai]]'' || Namit Khanna || ||\n|-\n| 2018 || ''[[Soorma (film)|Soorma]]'' || Bikramjeet Singh || ||\n|-\n| 2019 || ''[[The Zoya Factor (film)|The Zoya Factor]]'' ||Robin Rawal|| ||\n|-\n| 2020 || ''[[Gunjan Saxena]]'' || Anshuman Saxena ||\n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" width=60%\n!scope=\"col\" width=\"10%\"| Year\n!scope=\"col\"| Title\n!scope=\"col\"| Role\n!scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n!scope=\"col\" width=\"10%\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n|-\n| 2005 || ''[[Star One (Indian TV channel)|Cook Na Kaho]]'' || Host  || || <ref>https://www.tribuneindia.com/2005/20050529/spectrum/tv.htm</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2010 || ''[[Extraaa Innings T20]]  || Host || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Fear Factor: Khatron Ke Khiladi]]'' || Contestant || season 3 ||\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[Emotional Atyachar]]'' || Host || season 1 